author: roncosmeticchemist
text:
Do you really need a lip mask? ğŸ‘„ 

@beautystat cosmetic chemist review of Laneige lip sleeping mask 

The lips are a thin skinned area that are prone to dryness and chapping. 

The Laneige lip mask contains murumuru seed butter, shea butter, coconut oil and waxes to make it thick, rich and emollient on the lips.  
And this gummy bear flavor is powerful.

The key times to apply a lip treatment is after cleansing and before bed.
So a lip mask makes sense before you go to sleep.

But you can get similar results from any rich lip treatment.

I love rhode peptide lip treatment and Wyn Beauty by Serena Williams 

#lipmask
#laneige
#rhode 
#serenawilliams
